### Idea
Straight forward. Get size, k%size = offset. Then just find the new head by moving size - offset.
### Code
```
class Solution {
    public ListNode rotateRight(ListNode head, int k) {
        if (head == null) {
            return null;
        }
        int size = 1;
        ListNode tail;
        for (tail = head; tail.next != null; tail = tail.next) {
            size++;
        }
        int move = k % size;
        if (move == 0) {
            return head;
        }
        ListNode newTail = head;
        for (int i = 0; i < size - move - 1; i ++) {
            newTail = newTail.next;
        }
        ListNode newHead = newTail.next;
        newTail.next = null;
        tail.next = head;
        return newHead;
    }
}
```
