## Idea
Store the element in an array and use an int variable to represent the actual size.

## Code
```
class CustomStack {
    int[] arr;
    int cur = 0;
    
    public CustomStack(int maxSize) {
        arr = new int[maxSize];        
    }
    
    public void push(int x) {
        if (cur < arr.length) {
            arr[cur++] = x;
        }
    }
    
    public int pop() {
        if (cur == 0) {
            return -1;
        }
        return arr[--cur];
    }
    
    public void increment(int k, int val) {
        for (int i = 0; i < Math.min(k, cur); i++) {
            arr[i] += val;
        }
    }
}
```

## Complexity
Time: push: O(1); pop: O(1); increment: O(min(k, cur))
Space: O(maxSize)

