## Idea
Use increasing monotonic stack. If the next element to push is smaller than the element at the top, find the largest elements that is smaller than the current element. Every elements between this largest element(exclusive) and the current element(inclusive) will be considered in a chunk and we push the largest one among these elements back to the stack.

## Code
```
class Solution {
    public int maxChunksToSorted(int[] arr) {
        Stack<Integer> s = new Stack<>();
        int num = 0;
        for (int i = 0; i < arr.length; i++) {
            if (!s.isEmpty()) {
                if (arr[i] >= s.peek()) {
                    s.push(arr[i]);
                }
                else {
                    int max = -1;
                    while (!s.isEmpty() && s.peek() > arr[i]) {
                        max = Math.max(max, s.pop());
                    }
                    s.push(max);
                }
            }
            else {
                s.push(arr[i]);
            }
        }
        return s.size();
    }
}
