## 297. 二叉树的序列化与反序列化

## 题意
题目话有点多，简述一下题意
  - serialize(binary tree A) => string A
  - deserialize(string A) => binary tree A

## 思路
- 序列化：DFS + 先序遍历，构建当前树的字符串
  - 细节：null 节点，也要在字符串中占位
- 反序列化：字符串拆成数组后，按照先序遍历的顺序，构建二叉树
  - 每次从数组中剔除首节点：
  - 遇 null 字符串，返回 null
  - 遇数字字符串，构建树

## 改进
- 时间复杂度高
  - 上述思路，每次从字符串数组中剔除首节点，时间复杂度高 O(N)
- 如何改进
  - 序列化时反着来，原本二叉树字符串的构建顺序为「中、左、右」，改为「右、左、中」
  - 反序列化时，不剔除首节点，反过来剔除尾节点（时间复杂度为 O(1)

## 复杂度
- 时间：O(N)
- 空间：O(N)
  
## 代码
```javascript
/**
 * Definition for a binary tree node.
 * function TreeNode(val) {
 *     this.val = val;
 *     this.left = this.right = null;
 * }
 */

/**
 * Encodes a tree to a single string.
 *
 * @param {TreeNode} root
 * @return {string}
 */
const serialize = (root) => {
  if (root == null) {
    return 'n';
  }
  return serialize(root.right) + ',' + serialize(root.left) + ',' + root.val; 
};


/**
 * Decodes your encoded data to tree.
 *
 * @param {string} data
 * @return {TreeNode}
 */

var deserialize = (data) => {
  let list = data.split(',');

  const buildTree = () => {   
    const val = list.pop();
    if (val === 'n') {
      return null;
    }
    const root = new TreeNode(+val); 
    root.left = buildTree();       
    root.right = buildTree();       
    return root;                       
  };

  return buildTree(); 
};


/**
 * Your functions will be called as such:
 * deserialize(serialize(root));
 */
```

## 1. Two Sum

## Solution 1: hash map
### Iteration
- Use a hash map to store the index of each element and their substrahend. 
- If the substrahend of each element is alreay stored in our hash map, we get the answer
### Complexity
- time: O(n)
- space: O(n)
### Code
```javascript
/**
 * @param {number[]} nums
 * @param {number} target
 * @return {number[]}
 */
var twoSum = function(nums, target) {
  const sumCache = {};
  for (let i = 0; i < nums.length; i++) {
    const currNum = nums[i];
    const targetMinus = target - currNum;
    if (sumCache[targetMinus] !== undefined) {
      return [sumCache[targetMinus], i];
    }
    sumCache[currNum] = i;
  }
  return [];
};
```

## Solution 2: Two Pointer
### Set up
- make sure the given array is sorted
- set up two pointers that are at the two ends of the sorted array (right end, left end)
### Iteration
- iterate the sorted array, sum the values at the two pointers
  - sum == target
    - return [left, right]
  - sum > target
    - move the right pointer one step to the left side 
    - REASON: this will reduce the next sum, coz the array is sorted from left to right, aka smallest to largest
  - sum < target
    - move the left pointer one step to the right side

### Complexity
- time: O(n)
- space: O(n)
### Code
```javascript
/**
 * @param {number[]} nums
 * @param {number} target
 * @return {number[]}
 */
var twoSum = function(nums, target) {
  const iterNums = nums.slice();
  iterNums.sort((a, b) => a - b);

  let l = 0, r = nums.length - 1;
  for (let i = 0; i < nums.length; i++) {
    const left = iterNums[l];
    const right = iterNums[r];
    const currSum = left + right;
    if (currSum === target) { // at most happened once
      const ans = [];
      for (let j = 0; j < nums.length; j++) {
        if (nums[j] === left || nums[j] === right) ans.push(j);
      }
      return ans;
    }
    currSum < target ? l++ : r--;
  }
  return [];
};
```

