## 997. Find the Town Judge
## Solution
- The key to solve this problem is to focus on the two conditions: 
  - The town judge trusts nobody.
  - Everybody (except for the town judge) trusts the town judge.
- We will build two arrays to record how people trust others and how they are trusted by others. If someone is the judge:
  - that person will have n - 1 people that trust him/her.
  - that person will trust 0 others. 

## Complexity
- Time：O(N)
- Space: O(N)
## Code
```javascript
/**
 * @param {number} n
 * @param {number[][]} trust
 * @return {number}
 */
var findJudge = function(n, trust) {
    const trustedByOthersCount = new Array(n + 1).fill(0);
    const trustOthersCount = new Array(n + 1).fill(0);
    for (const trustInfo of trust) {
      ++trustOthersCount[trustInfo[0]];
      ++trustedByOthersCount[trustInfo[1]];
    }

    for (let i = 1; i <= n; i++) {
      if (trustedByOthersCount[i] === n - 1 && trustOthersCount[i] === 0) {
        return i;
      }
    }
    return -1;
};
```

