## Idea
Two pointer (slow & fast): traverse the list with different pace to find the meeting point
(no cycle if fast pointer reach to the tail)
Let head to first point into cycle be A; first point into cycle to meeting point B; meeting point to first point into cycle be C; Then 2(A+B) = A+B+C+B meaning A=C
Put slow pointer to the head and traverse the list with same pace. 
When two pointer meet again, we got the first point into cycle. 

## Code
```
public class Solution {
    public ListNode detectCycle(ListNode head) {
        ListNode slow = head;
        ListNode fast = head;

        while (fast != null && fast.next != null) {
            slow = slow.next;
            fast = fast.next.next; // diff pace
            if (slow == fast) {
                break; // meeting point
            }
        }

        if (fast == null || fast.next == null) { // if no cycle
            return null;
        }

        slow = head;
        while (slow != fast) {
            slow = slow.next;
            fast = fast.next; // same pace
        }
        return slow; // since A=C
    }
}
```
