# Day 3: 1381. Design a Stack With Increment Operation (stack)

- Problem Link
  - [1381. Design a Stack With Increment Operation](https://leetcode.com/problems/design-a-stack-with-increment-operation/)

- Ideas
  -  We could either use vanilla way to implement, or use an array to store the information. Use an additional array to record the increment value. inc[i] means for all elements stack[0] ~ stack[i], we should plus inc[i] when popped from the stack. Then inc[i-1]+=inc[i], so that we can accumulate the increment inc[i] for the bottom elements and the following pops.

- Complexity: hash table and bucket
  - Time: O(1)
  - Space: O(N)

- Code

```python
class CustomStack:

    def __init__(self, maxSize: int):
        self.list = []
        self.inc = [] #log inc value and add to the number when poping a number
        self.maxsize = maxSize

    def push(self, x: int) -> None:
        if len(self.list) < self.maxsize:
            self.list.append(x)
            self.inc.append(0)

    def pop(self) -> int:
        if not self.inc: return -1
        if len(self.inc) >1:
            self.inc[-2] += self.inc[-1]
        return self.list.pop() + self.inc.pop()

    def increment(self, k: int, val: int) -> None:
        if self.inc:
            self.inc[min(k, len(self.inc)) -1] +=val
