Key invariant: In each chunk, every element must greater than or equal to the maximum of the previous chunk.

I kept a stack storing the maximums of each chunk so far. Each new element starts out in its own chunk, then adjacent chunks are unioned together from right to left (via popping off of the stack and updating the maximum) until the above invariant is satisfied. 

```
class Solution {
    public int maxChunksToSorted(int[] arr) {
        Stack<Integer> maxInChunks = new Stack<Integer>();
        for (int x: arr) {
            int newMax = x;
            while (!maxInChunks.isEmpty() && maxInChunks.peek() > x) {
                newMax = Math.max(newMax, maxInChunks.pop());
            }
            maxInChunks.push(newMax);
        }
        return maxInChunks.size();
    }
}
```
Time complexity: O(n), since at most n-1 unions will take place

Auxiliary space: O(n)

